<item>
            <title>[SOLR-167] synonym filter mixes up terms from different synonyms</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-167</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SynonymFilter can mix up options from different synonyms, sometimes inserting the wrong word, sometimes using the wrong offset.  Issue appears to be use of the matched arraylist in SynonymFilter&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce: add &quot;best buy,bestbuy,bb&quot; to the example&apos;s synonym list.  Then view verbose analysis of the query analyzer output for &quot;Best buy - Acer Aspire AS5610-2273 - $599. Windows vista, 1 GB RAM&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;gigabytes&quot; becomes a synonym of &quot;Best buy&quot;, and the offsets of the remainder of the &quot;GB&quot; synonyms are incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assigning to Yonik as this code is too hairy for me to fix without further study.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
